// Skia Renderer
// SkiaRenderer paints the full editor frame each tick using CanvasKit (Skia/WASM): scene nodes, selection UI, snap guides, rulers, pen overlay, and remote cursors.
// synced: 2026-03-26T13:51:59Z

[Single class: SkiaRenderer. Owns a CanvasKit Surface and a pool of pre-allocated Paint objects.
 Coordinates: canvas-space (world) vs screen-space (pixels after pan/zoom). render() composes
 three layers: scene, section/component labels, UI overlays.
 Scene caching: the static scene is recorded as a SkPicture and replayed until sceneVersion changes
 or volatile overlays (hover, drop target, rotation preview) force a live redraw.
 Image fills and vector paths are cached (imageCache, vectorPathCache) and must be explicitly invalidated.]

FUNCTION constructor(ck, surface) [2026-03-26]
  Allocates all Paint objects once (fill, stroke, selection, snap, ruler, pen tool paints).
  Uses system font initially; proper Inter typeface installed after loadFonts().

---

FUNCTION loadFonts() -> Promise<void> [2026-03-26]
  CALLS: initFontService, loadFont (fonts)
  Async: loads Inter Regular, builds CanvasKit Typeface + FontMgr, replaces all size-variant
  Font objects (text/label/size/section title/component label), invalidates the scene picture.

---

FUNCTION invalidateScenePicture() [2026-03-26]                                        EXPORT
  Deletes the cached SkPicture, forcing a full scene re-record on the next render call.

---

FUNCTION invalidateVectorPath(nodeId) [2026-03-26]                                    EXPORT
  Deletes the cached Skia Path for a vector node (call after vectorNetwork changes).

---

FUNCTION render(graph, selectedIds, overlays, sceneVersion) [2026-03-26]              EXPORT
  CALLS: renderNode (self), drawSectionTitles, drawComponentLabels, drawSelection,
         drawSnapGuides, drawMarquee, drawLayoutInsertIndicator, drawPenOverlay,
         drawRemoteCursors, drawRulers (self)
  Main entry point. Three canvas layers (each save/restore):
    1. World layer (pan+zoom transform): scene nodes via SkPicture cache or live renderNode.
    2. Label layer (screen coords): section titles + component labels.
    3. UI overlay layer (screen coords): selection handles, snap guides, marquee, pen, cursors, rulers.
  Flushes surface at end.

---

FUNCTION renderSceneToCanvas(canvas, graph, pageId) [2026-03-26]                      EXPORT
  Disables viewport culling and renders all nodes directly to the given canvas.
  Used for PNG/SVG export (no overlays).

---

FUNCTION renderNode(canvas, graph, nodeId, overlays, parentAbsX, parentAbsY) [2026-03-26]
  Recursive scene painter. Per node:
    - Viewport cull: skip if AABB (expanded for rotation) is outside worldViewport.
    - Translate to node.x/y; apply opacity layer if < 1; apply rotation.
    - Dispatch to renderSection, renderComponentSet, or renderShape.
    - Draw text-edit overlay, drop-target highlight, hover outline if active.
    - Recurse into children; clip to node rect if clipsContent is true.

---

FUNCTION renderShape(canvas, node, graph) [2026-03-26]
  Paints a standard node: fills (via applyFill), drop shadows, strokes (with cap/join/dash),
  then inner shadows/blur effects. Dispatches fill/stroke drawing per node type.

---

FUNCTION applyFill(fill, node, graph, fillIndex) [2026-03-26]
  CALLS: resolveFillColor (self), applyGradientFill, applyImageFill (self)
  Sets fillPaint shader/color for SOLID, GRADIENT_*, or IMAGE fill types.

---

FUNCTION applyGradientFill(fill, node) [2026-03-26]
  Converts Figma gradient transform matrix to CanvasKit shader coordinates for
  LINEAR, RADIAL, ANGULAR (sweep), and DIAMOND (approximated as radial).

---

FUNCTION applyImageFill(fill, node, graph) [2026-03-26]
  Decodes image from graph.images on first use (cached in imageCache). Computes
  source rect for FILL (cover) and FIT modes, builds a cubic image shader.

---

FUNCTION resolveFillColor / resolveStrokeColor [2026-03-26]                           EXPORT
  Checks node.boundVariables for a variable binding; resolves via graph.resolveColorVariable.
  Falls back to the raw fill/stroke color.

---

FUNCTION buildParagraph(node, color?) -> Paragraph [2026-03-26]                       EXPORT
  CALLS: getTextAlign, textDecorationValue (self)
  Builds a CanvasKit Paragraph from the node's text, applying base style and any StyleRun
  overrides. Lays out at node.width. Caller must delete() the returned paragraph.

---

FUNCTION renderEffects(canvas, node, rect, hasRadius, pass) [2026-03-26]
  'behind' pass: renders DROP_SHADOW by offsetting a blurred copy of the node shape.
  'front' pass: renders INNER_SHADOW by clipping to the node shape and drawing an
  inverted blurred rect punched out with path difference.

---

FUNCTION drawSelection(canvas, graph, selectedIds, overlays) [2026-03-26]
  Single selection: draws full handle set (8 handles + rotation handle above) via drawNodeSelection.
  Multi-selection: draws per-node outlines + a dashed group bounding box with corner/edge handles.
  Uses component purple color for COMPONENT/INSTANCE/COMPONENT_SET nodes.

---

FUNCTION drawSectionTitles(canvas, graph) [2026-03-26]
  Collects visible SECTION nodes, draws a pill label above (or inside if nested).
  Truncates with ellipsis if wider than the section. Uses section fill color with
  luminance-based text contrast.

---

FUNCTION drawComponentLabels(canvas, graph) [2026-03-26]
  Draws a diamond icon + name label above (or inside for variants in a COMPONENT_SET)
  for all COMPONENT, COMPONENT_SET, and INSTANCE nodes in view.

---

FUNCTION hitTestSectionTitle(graph, canvasX, canvasY) -> SceneNode | null [2026-03-26] EXPORT
  Walks the tree to find whether (canvasX, canvasY) falls inside a section title pill.
  Used to detect section-rename clicks before hit-testing nodes.

---

FUNCTION hitTestComponentLabel(graph, canvasX, canvasY) -> SceneNode | null [2026-03-26] EXPORT
  Same as hitTestSectionTitle but for component/instance labels.

---

FUNCTION drawPenOverlay(canvas, penState) [2026-03-26]
  Renders the in-progress pen tool path: cubic bezier segments, preview line to cursor,
  tangent handle lines + circles, vertex dots (first vertex enlarged when closingToFirst).

---

FUNCTION drawRemoteCursors(canvas, graph, cursors) [2026-03-26]
  For each remote peer: draws selection outlines in peer color, a Figma-style arrow cursor,
  and a colored pill name badge.

---

FUNCTION drawRulers(canvas, graph, selectedIds) [2026-03-26]
  Draws horizontal and vertical pixel rulers with adaptive tick step (rulerStep).
  Highlights the selection range and renders coordinate badges at selection edges.

---

FUNCTION screenToCanvas(sx, sy) -> {x, y} [2026-03-26]                                EXPORT
  Converts screen pixel coordinates to world/canvas coordinates via pan and zoom.

---

FUNCTION destroy() [2026-03-26]                                                        EXPORT
  Deletes all CanvasKit objects (paints, fonts, image cache, vector path cache, surface).
